review_translated_text: This is no longer the place of Google Photos. The family-owned Poseidon Tavern is now located here. It's an atmospheric place with delicious, cheap food compared to the places around. I wholeheartedly recommend the delicious salads and seafood, especially mussels. The waiter is a 10-year-old fantastic boy who pays attention to every approach to the customer. Tip for him is pure pleasure.

To accompany the coffee, he invited us to some delicious dried fruit pastries.  we left wanting to return.  highly recommended.

review_id: Punto di ritrovo dei tifosi del Partizani Tirana, quest'anno squadra campione di Albania. Posto accogliente, addobbato con i colori e le bandiere della squadra della capitale! All'interno si possono trovare fotografie appese di tutti o quasi i tifosi del Partizani e anche un quadro in onore di Pano, leggenda della squadra albanese. Consiglio la visita agli amanti del calcio che si trovano a Tirana.
review_text: Punto di ritrovo dei tifosi del Partizani Tirana, quest'anno squadra campione di Albania. Posto accogliente, addobbato con i colori e le bandiere della squadra della capitale! All'interno si possono trovare fotografie appese di tutti o quasi i tifosi del Partizani e anche un quadro in onore di Pano, leggenda della squadra albanese. Consiglio la visita agli amanti del calcio che si trovano a Tirana.
review_translated_text: Meeting point for the fans of Partizani Tirana, this year the champion team of Albania. Cozy place, decked out in the colors and flags of the capital's team! Inside you can find hanging photographs of all or almost all Partizani fans and also a painting in honor of Pano, legend of the Albanian team. I recommend the visit to football lovers who are in Tirana.

review_id:
Embelsire me pete dhe portokall... an orange cake traditional in Sarande, Albania. This delicious treat was baked by Elga, who owns the Kafe Bar. Elga makes beautiful coffees and wonderful sweets!

Kind and generous, Elga made sure we found our hotel when we discovered there was no address listed in our booking confirmation and that our phones couldn't complete a call. Despite our language barrier, she figured out what we needed, took the initiative, called the hotel for us, and asked them to come pick us up. :)

We love you, Elga!
